abstract: CLEVELAND, Ohio, Oct. 13. For the first time since 1872 the Republicans of Cleveland are this evening canonading and burning fireworks over a political victory. It is only since the pressure of anxiety has been relieved this afternoon, by reports so complete as to leave no doubt of the election of Hayes, that they have begun to realize the importance and value of their triumph.
